name: Winter MQ
description: NOTE 2025: Due to constructions, the curling is located outside the MQ, by the Mariahilfer Straße. Inside the courtyard there are still a few drink stands and decorative lights.

name: Weihnachtsmarkt am Spittelberg
description: A local favorite! This cozy market winds through narrow cobblestone streets, offering shopping at artisan stalls, plus plenty of food and drink. Go early before it gets crowded.

name: Weihnachtsmarkt im Türkenschanzpark
description: A true locals' market in a quiet neighborhood park. The gastronomy is the star here, with offers ranging from traditional Christmas treats, to Spanish tapas - look out for pineapple punch!

name: Weihnachtsdorf am Stephansplatz
description: Enjoy the backdrop of the famous St. Stephen's Cathedral at this centrally-located market. Either go early to avoid the crowds, or sneak away to the nearby Haas & Haas.

name: Weihnachtsdorf am Campus der Universität Wien
description: Tucked away in the courtyard of the university, this low-key market is great for group gatherings. There's a bit of shopping, a few kids rides, and curling, making it perfect for everyone.

name: Weihnachtsmarkt Am Hof
description: This central market has some unique traits, including medieval-style mugs, a champagne bar, and a tree of dangling lights.

name: Weihnachtsmarkt in den Blumengärten Hirschstetten
description: The trek to this locals-only market is worth it - both the indoor and outdoor gardens are decorated, and the drinks are on the cheaper side.

name: Weihnachtsdorf Schloss Belvedere
description: The highlight of this market is the beautiful backdrop of the Belvedere Palace. Check out the reflection of the facade and Christmas lights on the garden's pond.

name: Altwiener Christkindlmarkt Freyung
description: Insider tip: grab a drink, and enjoy it by the adjacent fountain. You'll have more space while enjoying the festive atmosphere.

name: Art Advent - Kunst & Handwerk am Karlsplatz
description: This massive market offers something for everyone. There are shopping stalls with handcrafted items, stands with food and drink, and farm animals!

name: Kultur- und Weihnachtsmarkt Schloss Schönbrunn
description: This famous Christmas market is one of the largest. From ice skating to kids rides, to shopping and curling, there's plenty to do. Plus it's set in front of the beautiful Schönbrunn Palace.

name: Wiener Christkindlmarkt auf dem Rathausplatz
description: The most famous Christmas market in Vienna. Best to go at night when the Christmas lights are on full display!

name: Wintermarkt am Riesenradplatz
description: This smaller market is located directly in the amusement park, and looks on to the famous Ferris Wheel.

name: Haas & Haas - Winter in the City
description: A hidden gem right next to the cathedral! This small cozy courtyard has decorations, fireplaces, and a freshly grilled würstel!

name: Atmosphere Rooftop - Winter Terrace
description: This exclusive rooftop has almost 360 views of the city center. Go at dusk to best see Vienna's iconic landmarks, as you sip pricey drinks by Christmas trees and warm heaters.

name: Weihnachtsmarkt am Franz-Jonas-Platz
description: The options at this market are quite limited. If you need to pass through Floridsdorf, it can be seen rather quickly.

name: WIENterzauber - Marx Halle
description: This market is focused mainly on the shopping, with several artisanal stands selling unique gifts.

name: Weihnachten am Hauptbahnhof
description: Stop by this small stop before or after your train journey. There's a few drink and food options, and the train station Christmas lights in the background.

name: Adventmarkt im Verkehrsmuseum Remise 2025
description: A lovely local market in front of the tram museum! There are decorated trams on display, with some offering indoor seating and drinks. There's crafts for children, live music, and a complimentary postcard stand where you can send seasonal postcards throughout Austria free of charge!

name: Simmeringer Christkindlmarkt
description: While small, this local Christmas market is covered in decorations. The church next to it is lit with stars, there's a Christmas tree, and each stand has its own lights and garland. It's cozy and festive!

name: Weihnachtszauber Meidlinger Platzl
description: The smallest market on this list, with just one drink stand. Not a must, unless you happen to be there.

name: Lions Club Punschstand
description: Drink for a good cause! The proceeds made at this stand go towards charitable projects. It's in a quiet spot in the city center, and they offer free snacks.

name: Bärlipunsch - Puschhütte
description: A hidden gem! This stand-alone Punsch hut has cute decorations, and sells drinks to go. Or, if there's space, you can go drink inside their well-decorated hut!

name: PIAZZZA X-MAS Winterstories
description: New for 2025! A winter market playing 80's and 90's music right in the city center. Plus there's a Punsch Happy Hour Mon-Thu from 14:00-17:00

name: Punsch Karitativ
description: Enjoy a drink in this cobblestone piazza. This stand offers drinks and snacks, while a stand across from it offers hot chocolate - take you pick!
